{"lemma":"غُولٌ","slug":"غُولٌ","root":"غ.#.ل","root_slug":"غ-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غُولٌ","root":"غول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32656"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ape, orangutan","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ghoul, desert demon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"demon, jinn, goblin, monster"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ogre, cannibal, troll, oni, giant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calamity, disaster"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"taking away, snatching, seizing, grabbing"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root غ و ل (ḡ w l), related to غَالَ (ḡāla, “to seize”).\nCompare Sumerian [script needed] (gula, “great”).\n\nVerbal noun of غَالَ (ḡāla, “to snatch, to grab, to take away”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32656","headword_ar":"غُولٌ","root":"gwl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goblin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demon, devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jinnee, which, the Arabs assert, appears to men in the desert, assuming various forms, causing them to wander from the way, and destroying them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM, and TA * on the authority of IAth;) but this the Prophet denied, saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA guwla","text_ar":"لَا غُولَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; by which, however, accord. to some, he did not mean to deny the existence of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gwl","text_ar":"غول"},{"kind":"text","text":", but only the assertion of the Arabs respecting its assuming various forms and its being able to cause any one to go astray: (IAth, JM, * TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siEolaApN","text_ar":"سِعْلَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siEolaAp","text_ar":"سِعْلَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male jinnee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the female being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siEolaAp","text_ar":"سِعْلَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Abu-l-Wefee ElAarábee, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agowaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giylaAnN","text_ar":"غِيلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giwalapN","text_ar":"غِوَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) and it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an enchantress of the jinn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a demon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devil, that eats men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any jinnee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animal of prey, that destroys a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"terrible"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in appearance"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having tusks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fangs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen by the Arabs, and known by them; and killed by Taäbbata Sharrà:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as varies in form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance, of the enchanters"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the jinn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) on his doing which, as is said in a trad., one should hastily utter the call to prayer, to prevent his mischief by the mention of God: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything by reason of which the intellect departs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawolN","text_ar":"غَوْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that takes a man unexpectedly and destroys him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb:) [whence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaDabu guwlu AlHilomi","text_ar":"الغَضَبُ غُولُ الحِلْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anger"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is that which"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does away with, forbearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Destruction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the decree of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See 1, second sentence. ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAy^ilapN","text_ar":"غَايِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) of which latter the pl. in this sense is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawaAy^ilu","text_ar":"غَوَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA;) thus mentioned by Ks. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agowaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) accord. to Az, the Arabs call serpents"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agowaAl","text_ar":"اَغْوَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus this word is said to mean in the verse of Imra-el-Keys,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"liyaqotulaniY waAlma$orafiY~u muDaAjiEiY\n                      \n                     \n                        wamasonuwnapN zuroqN kaA^anoyaAbi A^agowaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To slay me, while the Meshrefee"},{"kind":"text","text":"sword"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was my bedfellow, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"so were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpened, polished"},{"kind":"text","text":"arrowheads,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the fangs of serpents"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA: *) but AHát says that this is meant as an exaggeration: (TA:) and it is said that the poet here means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devils."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}